1775833798594032	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE38Qs		item.create	bn-1582	{"description":"Apply measurement-driven performance improvements to bones, inspired by fff.nvim (~/repos/fff.nvim), a Rust-backed fuzzy finder optimized for sub-100ms latency on massive codebases.\n\nMethodology (per /extreme-performance):\n1. MEASURE FIRST — profile current hot paths before changing anything. No speculative optimization.\n2. Establish benchmarks with criterion for each target area (search, triage, TUI list, projection replay).\n3. Set concrete targets per task (e.g., 'triage over 10k bones under 20ms p99').\n4. Implement one change at a time; re-benchmark; accept only if measurable win.\n5. Track RSS alongside latency — the TUI 1.6GB RSS investigation is directly relevant.\n6. Prefer reversible, minimal changes; document why each technique was adopted or rejected.\n\nChild tasks capture individual techniques mined from fff.nvim. Each must start with a measurement and end with a benchmark-backed verdict.","kind":"goal","title":"Extreme performance pass: mine fff.nvim techniques"}	blake3:4CE6JGlaBTN7dxnnoGCe-G1BeU4j3lbsTiczpLIYOU4
1775833808679160	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE38gs		item.create	bn-2ury	{"description":"PREREQUISITE for all other perf tasks. Cannot optimize without a baseline.\n\nDeliverables:\n- criterion benches in each target crate: bones-triage (scoring over N items), bones-search (query latency), bones-core (event replay, projection build), bones-cli TUI list render.\n- Fixture datasets at 1k / 10k / 100k items.\n- Baseline numbers committed to a benches/BASELINE.md with p50/p99 latency and peak RSS.\n- Flamegraph (cargo-flamegraph or samply) of: bn triage, bn search <term>, TUI keystroke loop.\n- Identify top 3 hot functions per path; these become the focus of later tasks.\n\nExit criteria: running 'just bench' (or equivalent) produces a reproducible report. No optimization work in this bone.","kind":"task","labels":["perf","measurement"],"parent":"bn-1582","size":"s","title":"Baseline profiling + criterion harness for hot paths"}	blake3:DOytU-auq46jc-65kL-eOrqPJ-T_I_2kNl1p1QzBM2Q
1775833818872827	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE38ws		item.create	bn-1ylg	{"description":"Source: fff.nvim crates/fff-core/src/score.rs:474\n\nCurrent assumption: TUI list fully sorts all candidates per keystroke. For paginated views (visible rows << total), O(n) nth-element + sort-the-page is strictly cheaper.\n\nPlan:\n1. MEASURE: bench current TUI list update latency at 1k/10k/100k items (depends on bn-2ury baseline).\n2. Identify actual sort call site in TUI list render path.\n3. Replace full sort with select_nth_unstable_by for visible window, then sort just the window.\n4. Re-bench. Accept only if >20% win at 10k, or any measurable win at 100k.\n5. Verify no visual regression (sort stability where needed).\n\nExpected: large win at 100k, marginal at 1k. Reject if not.\n\nDepends on: bn-2ury.","kind":"task","labels":["perf","tui"],"parent":"bn-1582","size":"s","title":"TUI: partial sort via select_nth_unstable_by for paginated list"}	blake3:SfeWGf6N7hPQfLwnaYLB8BnZczCZjOItXhrZjDamVis
1775833828751901	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE39As		item.create	bn-17xg	{"description":"Source: fff.nvim crates/fff-core/src/file_picker.rs:1717 (hint_allocator_collect)\n\nDirectly relevant to TUI 1.6GB RSS investigation (see memory/project_tui_memory_investigation.md).\n\nPlan:\n1. MEASURE: RSS over a long TUI session at baseline (5min, 30min idle after search). Record via /proc/self/status.\n2. Switch global allocator to mimalloc (feature-gated so benchmarks can A/B).\n3. Re-measure RSS and latency. Expect lower fragmentation, possibly small latency win.\n4. Add optional mi_collect(true) call after projection rebuild / large churn events (feature: mimalloc-collect).\n5. Re-measure RSS post-spike decay. Accept only if RSS materially drops without latency regression.\n6. Document findings vs jemalloc for comparison.\n\nExit: either merge with benchmarks, or write up why it didn't help and close.\n\nDepends on: bn-2ury.","kind":"task","labels":["perf","memory"],"parent":"bn-1582","size":"s","title":"mimalloc global allocator + post-churn collect hint"}	blake3:h9Mydhacpk1D91wLvUNLTQQrxQGZp7P635iW3YVLDns
1775833843167649	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE39Qs		item.create	bn-30ub	{"description":"Source: fff.nvim crates/fff-core/src/file_picker.rs:60 (BACKGROUND_THREAD_POOL)\n\nfff.nvim uses (total_cpus - 2) for indexing to keep UI responsive under load.\n\nPlan:\n1. MEASURE: bench TUI keystroke-to-render latency while a background projection rebuild runs. Establish worst-case stall.\n2. Audit bones for rayon / tokio pool usage. If none, this task may become 'introduce a bounded background pool'.\n3. Size pool at max(1, cpus-2). Dedicate separate (small) pool for UI-initiated work.\n4. Re-measure worst-case stall. Accept if p99 drops.\n5. Reject if bones has no concurrent background work (log finding, close bone).\n\nDepends on: bn-2ury.","kind":"task","labels":["perf","tui"],"parent":"bn-1582","size":"s","title":"Thread pool sizing: reserve 2 cores for TUI event loop"}	blake3:EnUa_hVqHktdxdtO2AdUJmJo9D7rbtIN0cT909Lw3LU
1775833850716021	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE39gs		item.create	bn-1vyj	{"description":"Source: fff.nvim workspace Cargo.toml + bigram_filter.rs (ahash everywhere internal)\n\nLow-risk micro-optimizations. Only justified if allocations show up in flamegraph.\n\nPlan:\n1. MEASURE: allocation profile of bn search / bn triage via dhat or heaptrack. Confirm query-path allocs are non-trivial.\n2. Identify constraint lists, query part vectors, small caches — candidates for SmallVec<[_; 4]> and ahash::AHashMap.\n3. Apply changes only where a hot-path allocation or hash call is visible in the profile.\n4. Re-bench. Accept only if measurable (>5%) win or visible alloc count drop.\n5. Do NOT sprinkle SmallVec/ahash broadly — surgical only.\n\nDepends on: bn-2ury.","kind":"task","labels":["perf","search"],"parent":"bn-1582","size":"s","title":"SmallVec + ahash in query hot path"}	blake3:H2tTfWbRC_rDQ3RiT33AVI7EZRnQj2wCb6fWEZp12yI
1775833859752043	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE39ws		item.create	bn-pu4y	{"description":"Source: fff.nvim crates/fff-core/src/bigram_filter.rs (entire file)\n\nInverted bitset index over consecutive and skip-1 character bigrams. AND posting lists to eliminate ~99% of candidates before expensive fuzzy scoring. Drops sparse (<3.1%) and ubiquitous (>90%) columns.\n\nPlan:\n1. MEASURE: current bn search latency at 1k/10k/100k bones on realistic queries. Profile the scoring loop.\n2. Only proceed if scoring is demonstrably the bottleneck. Otherwise close as 'not warranted'.\n3. Build bigram index over title + body + labels. Store as Vec<u64> bitsets at fixed stride (SoA layout).\n4. Add query-time AND pass before scoring.\n5. Bench end-to-end. Target: >10x at 10k, approaching 100x at 100k.\n6. Memory cost budget: index should not exceed 2x the raw text size.\n\nHigher effort — gate on baseline showing search is actually slow.\n\nDepends on: bn-2ury.","kind":"task","labels":["perf","search"],"parent":"bn-1582","size":"m","title":"Bigram + skip-1 prefilter for bn search"}	blake3:2AvPDMaLk0LYSHR0jX8TTVmXV0_jgt-TAjH1Ge2RHi0
1775833870849439	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3-As		item.create	bn-3f00	{"description":"Source: fff.nvim crates/fff-core/src/bigram_filter.rs:459 (BigramOverlay)\n\nImmutable base index + AHashMap<idx, Vec<u16>> overlay for modified entries + tombstone bitset. Avoids rebuilding the full index on each change.\n\nConceptual fit for bones: immutable historical event log + overlay for recent events, so projections don't replay from scratch.\n\nPlan:\n1. MEASURE: current projection rebuild latency vs event log size. Identify whether this is actually a hot path or a cold path.\n2. If cold (<10ms at realistic sizes), close as 'not warranted — cost exceeds benefit'.\n3. If hot: design a base-snapshot + overlay scheme. Base = immutable snapshot at a checkpoint; overlay = events since checkpoint.\n4. Reject if CRDT semantics make overlay unsound (some events may retroactively touch old state).\n5. Bench before/after. Accept only with measurable win AND no correctness regression in sim.\n\nHigher risk — CRDT interactions. Depends on bn-2ury AND on search task findings.","kind":"task","labels":["perf","core"],"parent":"bn-1582","size":"m","title":"Bigram overlay pattern for incremental projection updates"}	blake3:FD2FhxHff__-9AMv_g1Sj-FaYnJ6O8DBoLQD53cjtU4
1775833879297224	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3-Qs		item.create	bn-3mof	{"description":"Source: fff.nvim crates/fff-core/src/frecency.rs (lines 260-309, 437-459)\n\nTracks access timestamps as VecDeque<u64>, scores via bracketed interpolation (2min→16, 15min→8, 1hr→4, 1day→2, 1week→1). Background GC via fresh-env rewrite. Persisted in LMDB.\n\nPlan:\n1. Confirm with user whether 'recently viewed/touched' should influence triage ranking. If no, close.\n2. MEASURE: current triage scoring cost and whether a new per-item lookup would dominate.\n3. Start with in-memory frecency table; skip LMDB until proven needed.\n4. Add bracketed scoring function (pure arithmetic, no alloc).\n5. Bench triage with/without frecency component. Confirm no significant slowdown.\n6. Only add LMDB persistence if cross-session frecency is actually desired.\n\nThis is a FEATURE dressed as perf — ensure it's wanted before implementing.\n\nDepends on: bn-2ury.","kind":"task","labels":["perf","triage"],"parent":"bn-1582","size":"m","title":"Frecency scoring with bracketed interpolation (+ optional LMDB persistence)"}	blake3:9SOUQbNUJh5WdGZJQSf6KswbtC6hspSFlzGv86LFVbU
1775833886495284	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3-gs		item.create	bn-125x	{"description":"Source: fff.nvim crates/fff-core/src/types.rs:70 (FileItem)\n\nSingle owned path string + u16 offsets (relative_start, filename_start) for zero-copy views. Saves per-item allocations.\n\nPlan:\n1. MEASURE: per-bone memory footprint via dhat or heaptrack. Quantify current String allocations per Issue.\n2. If allocations are <10% of memory cost, close as 'not warranted'.\n3. If meaningful: refactor Issue to store (text: Box<str>, title_end: u16, body_end: u16) with accessor methods returning &str slices.\n4. u16 caps each segment at 65535 bytes — verify this is acceptable (body length limit).\n5. Bench projection build + memory. Accept if RSS drops measurably.\n6. If RSS drops but accessor ergonomics suffer, document tradeoff and let reviewer decide.\n\nDepends on: bn-2ury.","kind":"task","labels":["perf","memory"],"parent":"bn-1582","size":"s","title":"String offset packing for Issue text fields"}	blake3:lDM_Tk54haooFHj1_gyI66JuSbxaKiR81C_mEHgNL74
1775833891423935	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3-ws		item.create	bn-1q3k	{"description":"Source: fff.nvim crates/fff-core/src/sort_buffer.rs + workspace Cargo.toml\n\nPer-thread reusable Vec<u8> scratch buffer for glidesort. Zero alloc per sort. Faster than stdlib on nearly-sorted data (typical between TUI keystrokes).\n\nPlan:\n1. MEASURE: identify all sort calls in hot paths via flamegraph (triage rank, TUI list, search result merge).\n2. For the hottest sort: A/B glidesort vs std::sort_unstable_by. Criterion bench.\n3. Only adopt glidesort where it shows >10% win on realistic fixtures.\n4. If adopted: add thread-local scratch buffer helper (RefCell<Vec<u8>>).\n5. Reject globally — only swap at specific call sites with evidence.\n\nLower priority — likely marginal. Depends on: bn-2ury and bn-1ylg (partial sort may supersede).","kind":"task","labels":["perf","sort"],"parent":"bn-1582","size":"s","title":"Evaluate glidesort with thread-local scratch buffers"}	blake3:XO0HC7imv_-pbiawk4zzLq7o2Qa4pvKYxDBbQDLVwtg
